Yeah. I already
went by her place,
she's not there.

04:15.506 --> 04:18.498
Look, if you see her,
call me, okay?

04:19.552 --> 04:21.133
Yeah. Thanks.

04:23.264 --> 04:24.470
(SIGHS)

04:25.474 --> 04:27.260
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

04:33.357 --> 04:34.437
Ma?

04:39.363 --> 04:41.399
Janice, honey, you home?

04:41.490 --> 04:42.900
Janice.

04:42.992 --> 04:44.027
SYLAR: Wow.

04:44.535 --> 04:46.617
Haven't you ever heard
of making two trips?

04:46.704 --> 04:49.821
Oh, God. Are you back
inside my head?

04:50.207 --> 04:51.538
(CHUCKUNG)

04:52.293 --> 04:55.660
That's so two months ago.
Here, let me give you a hand.

04:58.299 --> 05:01.462
Calm down, Parkman.
If I wanted you dead,
we wouldn't be talking.

05:01.552 --> 05:03.884
Then what the hell
do you want?

05:03.971 --> 05:05.802
lt's complicated.

05:06.307 --> 05:08.298
My life's taken a turn
since our time together.

05:08.392 --> 05:11.976
I suppose you could say
I'm on a fact-finding mission.

05:12.354 --> 05:14.140
Matt, honey.
MATT: Janice.

05:14.231 --> 05:16.062
Hey. I thought
you'd be at work
by now.

05:16.192 --> 05:18.649
Well, I took Matty
to day care,
my client canceled,

05:18.736 --> 05:20.601
so lucky I was home
because your friend Gabriel

05:20.696 --> 05:22.311
was in the neighborhood.

05:22.406 --> 05:24.692
He is full of stories.

05:24.825 --> 05:26.201
Stories?

05:26.660 --> 05:29.322
From when we were
partners on the force.

05:29.413 --> 05:31.495
So I figured that
you guys would
like to catch up,

05:31.582 --> 05:34.244
so I put a little
late lunch together.

05:34.710 --> 05:36.917
Looks so good.
Thank you.

05:37.379 --> 05:40.746
Parkman, take a load off.
Have a nosh.

05:41.717 --> 05:43.924
We really need
to catch up.

05:50.392 --> 05:53.520
You know, this is
probably not a good time.

05:54.563 --> 05:57.179
In fact, it's not
even a big deal.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.147
It's over. I don't
need to tell him.

05:59.235 --> 06:00.850
You kind of do.

06:00.945 --> 06:04.358
A super-powered serial killer
shape-shifted into a co-ed

06:04.448 --> 06:07.360
and then made
a pie chart
of your life.

06:07.785 --> 06:10.367
It wasn't a pie chart.
It was more like a...

06:10.454 --> 06:12.319
Whatever.
You have to
tell your dad.

06:12.414 --> 06:13.665
Really?

06:14.124 --> 06:17.958
'Cause when Sy|ar
killed my real dad,
he didn't tell me.

06:19.213 --> 06:22.956
I know.
You're right, but...

06:24.552 --> 06:26.383
I know. I know.

06:26.637 --> 06:28.218
"How long are you
gonna hold a grudge?

06:28.305 --> 06:31.388
"The whole silent treatment
is getting old."

06:32.810 --> 06:35.768
We were in a good place
before all this.

06:39.441 --> 06:41.727
Do you want me
to come with?

06:45.281 --> 06:46.566
Yes.

06:49.994 --> 06:53.111
No. This is something
I have to do alone.

06:55.583 --> 06:57.119
I could wait.

06:57.501 --> 06:59.583
It's probably
gonna be a while.

06:59.670 --> 07:02.503
The list of things
we have to talk about, Sy|ar,

07:03.007 --> 07:04.588
the cover-up
of my dad's death.

07:04.675 --> 07:05.915
Let's not forget
about the carnival.

07:06.010 --> 07:10.253
I'm sure there is plenty
my dad's been wanting
to say about that.

07:10.681 --> 07:11.921
Yeah.

07:13.183 --> 07:15.515
Well, good luck.

07:16.437 --> 07:18.598
You're gonna feel better
when it's all over with,

07:18.689 --> 07:21.476
or if not, at least
you'll be caffeinated.

07:55.476 --> 07:56.465
Claire?

07:56.560 --> 07:57.970
Lauren. Hey.

08:00.564 --> 08:02.395
You gonna let me in?

08:03.567 --> 08:05.307
Yeah. Of course.

08:14.370 --> 08:16.326
Where is my dad?

08:16.413 --> 08:19.029
He just stepped out
for a moment.

08:19.583 --> 08:21.574
I brought some coffee.

08:22.836 --> 08:26.044
I thought it was time
to talk things
over with him.

08:31.720 --> 08:35.679
I'm sorry, but why
are you here, exactly?

08:36.266 --> 08:37.597
(STUTTERS)

08:39.770 --> 08:41.681
Your father and l are...

08:41.772 --> 08:45.060
No, no. That's not
what I was talking about.

08:46.026 --> 08:51.441
I mean, you have
Primatech files
and satellite maps,

08:51.532 --> 08:57.152
and this is everything
that my dad said that
he would put behind him.

08:57.746 --> 08:59.702
Claire, I'm just trying
to help a friend.

08:59.790 --> 09:01.872
Friends do dinners
and movies.

09:01.959 --> 09:03.540
Okay, you wanna help?

09:03.627 --> 09:06.209
You tell my dad
whatever it is
that he's doing here,

09:06.296 --> 09:08.127
he needs to stop.

09:08.298 --> 09:10.289
I wish it was that simple.

09:10.384 --> 09:12.375
Why? What's going on?

09:13.470 --> 09:15.426
There was an incident.

09:15.889 --> 09:17.925
It was Samuel Sullivan.

09:26.817 --> 09:28.557
What did he do?

09:28.652 --> 09:32.236
They're saying
it was a landslide,
but we know it was Samuel.

09:32.322 --> 09:34.984
Wait. You think
he buried that town?

09:35.743 --> 09:37.654
Can he even do that?

09:37.786 --> 09:41.244
He gains more power
the more specials
he has around.

09:42.332 --> 09:45.574
Two hundred are dead,
and they're still
digging out the bodies.

09:45.669 --> 09:48.001
What are you
planning to do?

09:49.256 --> 09:51.918
You know, your dad's
gonna be back any minute.
Why don't you just take...

09:52.009 --> 09:54.170
Actually,
I have class.

09:55.345 --> 09:57.336
But it looks like
you guys have this
under control.

09:57.431 --> 09:59.046
Sojust tell him
I stopped by.

09:59.141 --> 10:00.221
Claire, wait.

10:00.309 --> 10:01.298
Enjoy the coffee.

10:01.393 --> 10:02.633
Claire.

10:02.728 --> 10:03.717
(SlGHS)

10:10.778 --> 10:13.110
I've always loved
the black and whites.

10:13.197 --> 10:14.778
Are they still
Matty's favorite?

10:14.865 --> 10:16.355
How'd you know that?

10:16.492 --> 10:19.780
Like I said, Parkman and I
used to be pretty tight
back in the day.

10:19.870 --> 10:23.454
We even went through
addiction
counseling together.

10:23.874 --> 10:25.535
We faced
our mutual demons.

10:25.667 --> 10:27.703
You know what, honey,
I'm gonna show Gabe here

10:27.836 --> 10:29.212
what I've been doing
in the basement.

10:29.338 --> 10:32.205
Yes. The wonderful
world of Matt's projects.

10:32.341 --> 10:33.797
You're gonna love it
down there.

10:33.884 --> 10:35.840
I'm sure I will.
(JANICE CHUCKLING)

10:45.562 --> 10:50.556
You're on
a "fact-finding mission".
What the hell does that mean?

10:51.401 --> 10:54.438
I had to make sure
I remembered it right.

10:54.822 --> 10:57.313
Husband and father.

11:00.369 --> 11:03.953
You've really figured out
a way to live
with your ability.

11:05.082 --> 11:07.619
You know,
you may not believe this,

11:08.043 --> 11:10.159
but in some ways
you're actually
stronger than I am.

11:10.254 --> 11:11.835
Look, I'm not
afraid of you, okay?

11:11.922 --> 11:13.287
So if this is
about revenge...

11:13.382 --> 11:16.545
Well, after
what you did to me,
I was tempted.

11:17.469 --> 11:20.461
But I don't want to be
that person anymore.

11:22.015 --> 11:24.472
I need you to go
inside my head again.

11:24.560 --> 11:25.845
(LAUGHING)

11:25.936 --> 11:27.722
You're serious?

11:28.522 --> 11:30.638
Wow. You are insane.

11:32.276 --> 11:36.064
If I am, it's because
that's what my powers
have made me.

11:36.822 --> 11:39.734
I can't live with them
anymore, Parkman.

11:40.409 --> 11:42.775
So you need to
take them away.

11:46.957 --> 11:48.743
You want me to...

11:49.042 --> 11:50.782
How am I supposed
to do that?

11:50.878 --> 11:53.039
You can create
a mental block,
repress them.

11:53.130 --> 11:55.542
I don't really care,
to be honest.

11:56.049 --> 12:00.042
All I know is that
once I'm free from the
temptation of my ability...

12:00.137 --> 12:02.469
Mmm-hmm.
You're gonna be normal?

12:02.556 --> 12:06.048
I'm sorry.
That ship sailed,
what, 50 murders ago.

12:06.727 --> 12:08.638
I'm asking nicely.

12:08.729 --> 12:10.094
The last time that
l was inside your head,

12:10.188 --> 12:12.270
you turned my life
into a living hell.

12:12.357 --> 12:14.393
What makes you think
I'm gonna risk that?

12:14.484 --> 12:16.816
Janice and the kid.

12:18.238 --> 12:20.320
I really do
want to change,

12:21.074 --> 12:24.032
but I'm insane,
remember?

12:25.746 --> 12:28.408
And all I have to do
is point.

12:29.917 --> 12:31.748
Fine. lwill try,

12:32.753 --> 12:35.210
but you have to
let Janice go.

12:39.217 --> 12:41.879
Consider it
a gesture of good faith.

12:50.062 --> 12:51.552
(DOOR CLOSING)

13:01.782 --> 13:03.318
Hey, Mom.

13:04.576 --> 13:05.816
What's wrong?

13:05.911 --> 13:07.776
Oh, it's Nathan.

13:08.205 --> 13:10.161
The stone-cutters called.

13:10.248 --> 13:13.035
They needed
the final wording
for his headstone,

13:13.126 --> 13:15.583
and I didn't know
what to say.

13:15.671 --> 13:18.128
lguess
it's the finality of it.

13:19.508 --> 13:23.467
I mean, they're just words,
but when you write them down,

13:23.595 --> 13:26.007
when you etch them
in stone...

13:26.765 --> 13:28.346
I know, Mom.

13:29.393 --> 13:33.636
Maybe it was selfish
of me, Peter, but
I just needed to see you.

13:33.730 --> 13:36.142
I needed to be sure
you were okay.

13:36.233 --> 13:38.315
Because of your vision?

13:39.820 --> 13:42.027
I had the dream, too, Mom.

13:42.781 --> 13:44.646
I saw all the people,

13:45.075 --> 13:46.406
and Sy|ar,

13:47.119 --> 13:49.735
I think he was trying
to help Emma.

13:51.623 --> 13:53.363
You saw that, too?

13:57.337 --> 14:00.875
Whatever this vision is,
Peter, remember this,

14:02.092 --> 14:06.051
one isolated act
does not make Sy|ar
your friend's savior.

14:17.899 --> 14:20.481
I need you to help me
find him, Mom.

14:20.610 --> 14:22.692
I know you know
where he is.

14:22.779 --> 14:25.441
Sy|ar's never been
far from my thoughts,

14:27.034 --> 14:29.275
but I'm begging you,
don't go.

14:29.703 --> 14:30.692
He murdered Nathan,

14:30.787 --> 14:33.529
and the last time
you faced him,
he almost killed you.

14:33.623 --> 14:35.454
Mom, Emma's in trouble.

14:35.542 --> 14:37.123
People's lives are at stake.

14:37.210 --> 14:40.043
Nathan would never
turn his back on them,

14:40.130 --> 14:41.836
and you know that
I can't either.

14:55.020 --> 14:56.760
This is gonna end badly.

14:56.855 --> 14:59.471
Samuel is crazy,
my dad's going to
take him down,

14:59.566 --> 15:02.774
and there's no way
this is going to
end well.

15:05.155 --> 15:07.737
What? What do you
want me to say?

15:08.492 --> 15:10.983
Well, what do you think
I should do?

15:12.037 --> 15:14.870
I don't know. You've got
a Humanities lecture
in 20 minutes.

15:14.956 --> 15:17.993
Here's a crazy idea.
Maybe you should go
to class for once.

15:18.085 --> 15:20.667
Did you hear anything
I just said?

15:22.672 --> 15:25.254
But, I mean,
what are you really
going to do, Claire?

15:25.342 --> 15:26.878
Your dad was right
about the carnival.

15:26.968 --> 15:29.675
You never should
have gone there.

15:29.763 --> 15:31.879
Samuel is a bad guy, yes,

15:31.973 --> 15:35.010
but the rest of the carnival
is all family and children.

15:35.102 --> 15:38.310
And they just want to
live their lives being open
about their abilities.

15:41.691 --> 15:43.818
But they don't know that.

15:44.111 --> 15:45.317
You were only there
for one day.

15:45.403 --> 15:48.611
How could you possibly
know for sure?

15:48.698 --> 15:50.734
I need to borrow your car.

15:50.826 --> 15:52.066
No.

15:53.203 --> 15:55.489
I thought you would
back me up on this.

15:55.580 --> 15:58.196
You say you want
a normal life, right?

15:58.291 --> 16:00.373
Just let your dad
handle it.

16:00.460 --> 16:03.543
Come on, please.
Just come to class with me.

16:05.048 --> 16:06.254
GRETCHEN: Or not.

16:07.259 --> 16:09.045
Bring it back full.

16:12.264 --> 16:13.470
(SlGHS)

16:16.059 --> 16:17.674
