turn yourself over.

19:13.862 --> 19:15.568
To your father?

19:16.740 --> 19:18.651
He's not exactly
known for his mercy.

19:18.742 --> 19:22.576
If you give yourself up,
he will not hurt you.
I promise.

19:24.080 --> 19:27.288
Please, Samuel,
listen to her.

19:28.918 --> 19:32.376
If you care
about this family,
then protect them.

19:43.058 --> 19:44.764
There's Samuel
on the midway.

19:48.938 --> 19:50.348
Got him.

19:54.861 --> 19:56.317
Wait a second.

19:56.404 --> 19:57.735
Is that Claire?

19:58.365 --> 19:59.946
At two o'clock.

20:11.669 --> 20:13.580
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

20:21.429 --> 20:22.669
Hello, Claire.

20:22.764 --> 20:24.220
Dad, where are you?

20:24.599 --> 20:25.805
Close.

20:26.226 --> 20:29.218
/ heard
you stopped by earlier.
Thanks for the coffee.

20:29.312 --> 20:31.553
What's the
situation there?

20:31.648 --> 20:33.639
Samuel wants
to surrender.

20:33.775 --> 20:35.311
Really? Why?

20:35.485 --> 20:37.476
To protect his family.

20:37.570 --> 20:38.901
He’s willing
to turn himself over

20:38.988 --> 20:42.822
as long as the rest
of the carnival stays safe
and under the grid.

20:42.951 --> 20:44.816
And you trust him?

20:45.662 --> 20:48.825
If there's a chance
that we can do this
without anyone getting hurt,

20:48.957 --> 20:50.948
don't we have to try?

20:53.503 --> 20:55.414
Dad, it's the best plan.

20:55.505 --> 20:58.918
All right? You get Samuel
and nobody gets hurt.

20:59.592 --> 21:00.752
All right.

21:00.844 --> 21:04.462
Tell him to meet us
in the field
outside of the carnival.

21:04.681 --> 21:06.672
I'll see you soon.

21:11.980 --> 21:13.766
He's surrendering.

21:14.691 --> 21:16.932
And you think
he's just gonna
give himself up?

21:17.026 --> 21:21.315
I don't know,
but Claire seems to think so
and l have to trust her.

21:21.531 --> 21:22.771
It's done.

21:22.866 --> 21:25.027
He wants you
to meet him
in the field.

21:27.036 --> 21:29.288
LAUREN: Are you sure
this is a good idea?

21:29.789 --> 21:31.029
You know what?

21:31.124 --> 21:33.536
If it's a setup,
you're just going to get
a better shot at him

21:33.626 --> 21:35.287
out in the open,
away from everybody.

21:35.378 --> 21:38.495
Wait a second.
I'll go down
and walk him out.

21:39.549 --> 21:41.710
Keep him
in the crosshairs.

21:42.010 --> 21:43.045
Hey,

21:43.887 --> 21:44.967
be careful.

22:00.945 --> 22:02.355
(lNAUDlBLE)

22:29.933 --> 22:31.639
(PEOPLE MUTTERING)

22:40.151 --> 22:42.563
I know my recent actions
have caused some of you

22:42.654 --> 22:45.361
to question where it is
that my heart lies.

22:49.452 --> 22:51.864
I regret what I've done.

22:53.248 --> 22:56.615
I acted impulsively
and that has brought
one of them,

22:57.293 --> 22:59.705
an agent, to our door.

23:00.672 --> 23:02.128
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
MAN 1: What?

23:02.215 --> 23:04.376
It's okay. It's okay.

23:04.467 --> 23:06.298
MAN 2: You wanna
just make it worse.

23:06.386 --> 23:08.126
They just want me.

23:09.389 --> 23:12.426
Claire has helped arrange
a peaceful surrender.

23:12.517 --> 23:14.303
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

23:14.394 --> 23:16.225
I'll go with them.

23:16.312 --> 23:18.428
No,no,no.
Please, listen.

23:19.440 --> 23:22.603
I know everyone
will not agree
to this decision,

23:23.236 --> 23:25.147
but it's the only way.

23:25.822 --> 23:28.859
The safety of each
and every one of you

23:28.950 --> 23:32.784
and keeping
this family together is
what matters most to me.

23:34.455 --> 23:37.583
And if that means
I have to leave,
so be it.

23:37.667 --> 23:38.907
(GROANS)

23:39.002 --> 23:40.663
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

23:41.588 --> 23:42.919
(GUNSHOTS)

24:05.069 --> 24:06.400
(COUGHING)

24:17.373 --> 24:19.159
All right, Parkman.

24:19.375 --> 24:21.627
I did my part.
I let Janice walk.
Now it's your turn.

24:21.711 --> 24:22.700
I know.

24:24.547 --> 24:26.879
I know.
I said I would try.

24:30.720 --> 24:31.880
(SlGHS)

24:39.103 --> 24:40.354
(GROANS)

24:46.402 --> 24:48.267
Nothing's changed.

24:50.031 --> 24:52.272
I know you can do this,
Parkman. What's wrong?

24:52.450 --> 24:53.906
I don't know.

24:54.744 --> 24:56.109
I don't know.

24:57.038 --> 24:59.495
Okay. Okay.

25:07.757 --> 25:09.042
(PANTING)

25:10.927 --> 25:12.508
I can't. I can't.

25:12.595 --> 25:13.835
Try again.

25:13.930 --> 25:15.921
Maybe it's not me.

25:16.015 --> 25:17.004
Sy|ar, come on.
Maybe it's you.

25:17.100 --> 25:18.180
Maybe you're
just fighting it.

25:18.267 --> 25:20.599
Maybe you really
don't want to let go
of these powers.

25:20.687 --> 25:21.972
No. You're lying.

25:22.063 --> 25:23.098
I'm not lying.

25:23.231 --> 25:24.687
JANICE: Matt, what's going on?
No!

25:24.774 --> 25:28.107
Stop! Stop! Oh, God.
Please let her go.

25:28.403 --> 25:30.519
Hey! Hey! Look at me.
Look at me.

25:30.613 --> 25:32.695
Come on. Let her go.
She had nothing
to do with this.

25:32.782 --> 25:35.649
Come on, let her go.
Let her go.
I'll try again. Come on.

25:35.743 --> 25:37.699
It's not good enough.

25:38.371 --> 25:39.360
(GROANING)

25:39.455 --> 25:40.831
You see
what you made me do?

25:40.915 --> 25:42.200
MATT: Hey!

25:42.291 --> 25:44.748
I don't even know
if I can do this for you.
Come on.

25:44.836 --> 25:47.794
Maybe you need
a little more motivation.

25:48.756 --> 25:51.623
You will purge me
of these powers, Parkman.

25:51.759 --> 25:53.420
Or I will use them.

25:54.470 --> 25:56.301
lwill use them all.

25:58.224 --> 25:59.680
And trust me,

26:00.435 --> 26:02.471
I can get really creative.

26:05.648 --> 26:06.808
No.

26:10.027 --> 26:11.983
(GUNSHOTS)

26:30.006 --> 26:31.337
(GROANING)

26:43.352 --> 26:44.683
Damn!

27:09.337 --> 27:11.373
Samuel, come quickly.

27:20.723 --> 27:24.341
No. No, no, no. No! No!

27:25.061 --> 27:26.221
No.

27:26.479 --> 27:30.563
You need to put
pressure on the wound.
I need your help. Come on.

27:32.819 --> 27:34.059
(GASPlNG)

27:42.954 --> 27:44.490
(TWIG SNAPPlNG)

28:15.820 --> 28:17.481
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

28:27.748 --> 28:30.615
You wanted to know
what was in my heart.

28:36.799 --> 28:38.084
(GASPlNG)

28:46.976 --> 28:49.342
You did this?

28:50.938 --> 28:52.348
I'm sorry.

28:53.691 --> 28:55.101
I'm so sorry.

28:55.192 --> 28:56.272
(LYDIA SOBBING)

28:56.360 --> 28:58.316
I'm so sorry.

29:00.615 --> 29:02.480
They needed a villain,

29:03.159 --> 29:04.865
someone worse than me.

29:06.537 --> 29:08.823
You gave that to them.
Thank you.

29:24.263 --> 29:25.503
Watch out.

29:26.307 --> 29:27.547
Watch out.

29:27.642 --> 29:29.098
It's too late, Claire.

29:30.353 --> 29:31.809
She's gone.

29:33.981 --> 29:35.266
(SOBBING)

30:22.780 --> 30:25.487
Come on, Dad.
Pick up, please.

30:40.297 --> 30:41.582
ELI: Samuel!

30:43.175 --> 30:44.426
Dad.

30:46.846 --> 30:49.007
ELI: I found him
on the hill.

30:51.267 --> 30:52.382
With this.

30:52.476 --> 30:54.216
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

30:57.940 --> 30:59.020
Are you okay?

30:59.108 --> 31:01.099
Claire, I didn't do it.

31:01.444 --> 31:03.105
I didn't shoot.

31:03.487 --> 31:04.772
Murderer!

31:08.284 --> 31:10.775
You brought him here.
You're one of them.

31:10.870 --> 31:12.485
Hey! Back off.

31:20.296 --> 31:22.457
No. Don't hurt them.

31:22.882 --> 31:24.873
We're better than this.

31:29.138 --> 31:31.550
Take him to
the House of Mirrors.

31:32.266 --> 31:33.597
Tie him up.

31:41.984 --> 31:43.315
And her?

31:44.153 --> 31:45.643
My trailer.

31:47.698 --> 31:49.939
Get off! Get off!

31:50.034 --> 31:51.774
No!Dad!

31:51.869 --> 31:53.075
Dad!

31:53.829 --> 31:57.413
Let go! Samuel,
he didn't do it!

31:58.667 --> 32:00.658
Get off! Get off!

32:01.504 --> 32:03.119
If you hurt her,
I swear to God...

32:03.214 --> 32:04.454
That's the problem,
isn't it?

32:04.548 --> 32:05.799
One cruel thought
is all it takes.

32:05.883 --> 32:07.839
These powers
make it so easy.

32:07.927 --> 32:11.715
I understand that, believe me.
But you don't have to
use them like this.

32:11.847 --> 32:13.383
Except I do.

32:14.266 --> 32:16.177
The powers are me now.

32:16.936 --> 32:19.427
You've been there,
dealt with the abilities,
the constant temptation.

32:19.522 --> 32:21.513
Tell me, how do you
compartmentalize?

32:21.607 --> 32:24.314
How do you keep them
from overwhelming
the rest of your life?

32:24.401 --> 32:29.020
You start by accepting
the fact that you're more
than just your abilities.

32:30.866 --> 32:32.948
Come on,
we're people first.

32:33.035 --> 32:35.196
Please, let her go.

32:35.871 --> 32:37.202
(GROANING)

32:45.089 --> 32:47.125
Look, I'll try to do
what you want,

32:47.216 --> 32:49.548
but you got to give me
a couple of minutes,
make sure she's okay.

32:49.635 --> 32:51.375
Last chance, Parkman.

32:52.054 --> 32:53.385
MATT: Come on.

32:53.722 --> 32:54.848
It's okay. Come on.

32:54.932 --> 32:56.138
That's Sy|ar, wasn't it?

32:56.225 --> 32:58.056
I'm so sorry.

32:58.394 --> 32:59.930
This is crazy.

33:00.479 --> 33:03.642
He wants me
to take away his powers
and make him normal.

33:03.732 --> 33:05.472
Meanwhile, I looked
inside his head
long enough to realize

33:05.568 --> 33:07.229
that he's serious,
but I can't give him
what he wants.

33:07.319 --> 33:08.434
Well, forget
what he wants.

33:08.571 --> 33:12.234
I've worked with
monsters like this.
He's broken inside, Matt.

33:12.324 --> 33:16.738
We have to bury him
so that he cannot
hurt anyone else.

33:18.455 --> 33:19.661
Yeah, okay.

33:19.748 --> 33:23.081
Just go. Go.
And don't come back
until I call you.

33:24.461 --> 33:25.962
(DOOR CLOSING)

33:26.130 --> 33:28.337
All right,
get on with it.

33:28.424 --> 33:31.040
You were right.
I was holding back.

33:31.135 --> 33:33.251
It's all about motivation.

33:39.602 --> 33:41.718
GABRIEL:
What ifl told you
that I can be special?

33:41.812 --> 33:45.350
But to do it, I'd have to
hurt a lot of people.
Should I?

33:46.650 --> 33:49.266
You? You can never
hurt anyone.

33:49.945 --> 33:51.230
Mommy.

33:57.286 --> 33:59.277
(BOTH PANTING)

34:04.251 --> 34:06.458
I don't feel any different.

34:07.421 --> 34:10.288
Try something.
Go ahead. On me.
Come on.

34:17.806 --> 34:19.342
You did it.

34:20.935 --> 34:22.846
My powers are gone.
No, they're not gone.

34:22.937 --> 34:26.225
They're just buried
somewhere that you can
never get to them.

34:26.315 --> 34:29.057
You've threatened
my family for the last time.

34:29.151 --> 34:30.311
What did you do?

34:30.444 --> 34:33.277
I know exactly
what scares you,
Gabriel,

34:33.364 --> 34:35.355
and it's being alone
with your immortality.

34:35.491 --> 34:36.606
What did you do to me?

34:36.700 --> 34:39.316
I have trapped you
inside your twisted mind.

34:39.453 --> 34:42.536
You're gonna be alone,
Sy|ar, very much alone,

34:42.623 --> 34:45.865
in this nightmare
that will last forever.

34:45.960 --> 34:47.416
And the best part
about it is

34:47.503 --> 34:49.494
that when I leave here,
you're not gonna
remember what I did,

34:49.588 --> 34:52.625
and you're going to
live every empty day
like it's real.

34:52.716 --> 34:54.217
You said you would help me.

34:54.343 --> 34:57.801
Yeah. Well, I guess
there's still a little of you
left inside me,

34:57.888 --> 34:59.503
because I lied.

35:02.518 --> 35:04.008
Enjoy hell.

35:08.357 --> 35:09.688
Parkman?

35:14.989 --> 35:16.229
Parkman?

35:47.563 --> 35:48.723
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

35:48.814 --> 35:50.020
PETER: Matt?

35:52.901 --> 35:54.152
Matt!

36:30.105 --> 36:33.097
Samuel said you'd come.
Thank God you're here.

36:33.192 --> 36:35.057
He needs your help.

36:36.862 --> 36:38.363
(WOMAN CRYING)

36:40.407 --> 36:42.489
(SAMUEL CHUCKLES)

36:43.118 --> 36:45.951
Finally, there's a doctor
in the house.

36:46.914 --> 36:48.279
What happened?

36:48.374 --> 36:49.363
We were attacked.

36:49.458 --> 36:51.449
You were attacked?
By who?

36:52.127 --> 36:55.619
People who don't
understand us, Emma.

36:57.049 --> 36:58.710
People who fear us.

36:59.718 --> 37:01.458
It doesn't matter.

37:03.972 --> 37:06.554
What matters is
that you're here.

37:08.310 --> 37:10.972
You're notjust going
to heal me, Emma,

37:11.480 --> 37:15.314
you're going to help us
make a new world
for ourselves.

37:16.610 --> 37:17.816
Yeah.

37:17.903 --> 37:19.768
We'll show them, Emma.

37:21.740 --> 37:24.482
We'll show them
how great we can be.

37:31.500 --> 37:32.740
Matt?

37:34.503 --> 37:35.788
Matt!

37:40.759 --> 37:43.341
Hey, man. Sorry.
I was working downstairs.

37:43.470 --> 37:45.006
It's okay, man.
Been a long time.

37:45.139 --> 37:46.925
Yeah. How are you?

37:50.686 --> 37:51.721
What?

37:51.812 --> 37:52.927
Sy|ar is here.

37:53.021 --> 37:54.306
What are you talking about?

37:54.398 --> 37:56.514
I'm talking about
what you're thinking.

37:56.692 --> 37:58.523
You're gonna take him.
You can'tjust take him.

37:58.610 --> 38:01.022
People die, Matt.
Sy|ar has to save them.

38:01.113 --> 38:03.024
Peter, he's
a murderer. Hey!

38:04.116 --> 38:07.449
Come on, stop. Listen,
he's trapped, Peter.

38:09.746 --> 38:11.532
What the hell
did you do?

38:11.665 --> 38:14.702
I went inside his head
and I trapped him
in his worst nightmare.

38:14.793 --> 38:16.954
He'll never hurt
anyone again.

38:17.171 --> 38:18.286
I have to bring him back.

38:18.380 --> 38:19.790
No. No, you can't do that.

38:19.882 --> 38:21.213
You go into his head,
you might not come out.

38:21.300 --> 38:24.212
Peter! Peter, don't!
Peter! No! Peter!

38:40.277 --> 38:41.517
Matt!

38:53.999 --> 38:55.284
Hello!

38:59.421 --> 39:00.706
Hello!

39:06.053 --> 39:07.259
Hello!

39:14.102 --> 39:15.353
Hello!

39:18.106 --> 39:19.357
(WINCING)

39:30.160 --> 39:31.445
(RINGING)

39:37.084 --> 39:38.620
Tracy Strauss.

39:39.169 --> 39:42.753
Noah Bennet told me to call
if anything went wrong.

40:19.459 --> 40:21.165
I went to Bennet.

40:22.212 --> 40:23.452
I thought...

40:23.547 --> 40:25.538
Look what they've done.

40:26.008 --> 40:28.169
These so-called
normal people.

40:32.264 --> 40:34.755
How could you
let this happen?

41:01.960 --> 41:04.576
What I did was wrong,
I know that,

41:06.340 --> 41:10.049
but I was willing
to sacrifice myself
to protect you,

41:11.303 --> 41:14.841
to save this family
that we've all come to love.

41:15.807 --> 41:17.798
But the outside world
has proven once again

41:17.893 --> 41:21.260
that people like us
will never be accepted.

41:22.648 --> 41:24.559
We've all seen it

41:25.651 --> 41:28.768
in the eyes of those
who come to see our shows,

41:28.862 --> 41:31.023
dazzled by our abilities,

41:32.199 --> 41:35.783
but filled with revulsion
over who we are.

41:37.996 --> 41:39.987
I saw it again yesterday,

41:41.583 --> 41:43.995
in that small town
over the hill.

41:46.421 --> 41:50.881
And today, in the bullets
that struck me and
murdered our dear Lydia.

41:55.055 --> 41:56.591
It's time.

42:00.185 --> 42:03.018
It's time we put fear
behind us.

42:06.149 --> 42:08.265
It's time we show the world

42:10.070 --> 42:11.731
what we truly are.
